				\begin{document}$$\frac{{F}_{0}}{F}\,=\,1\,+\,{K}_{sv}\,[Q]$$\end{document}F0F=1+Ksv[Q][Q] is the concentration of the quencher (OEO/thymol). As it is shown in Fig. 11, Stern–Volmer plot was linear which indicated that the process is either static or dynamic quenching. Meanwhile, KSV was calculated 0. 50*102 and 1.25*102 M−1 for OEO and thymol respectively, which was not consistent with Ksv of intercalate mode. To more study the binding process, Kq, the bimolecular quenching rate constants, was calculated using the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
